UNIVERSAL EXECUTABLE SPEC TERM SHEET
(API BOT — RESILIENT, AUTONOMOUS, NASA POWER OF 10 COMPLIANT)

PURPOSE
- Define a single, unambiguous contract for building API-driven bots
- Eliminate implementation doubt for development teams
- Force resilient, failure-tolerant, self-contained behavior
- Produce code that does not break, does not drift, and degrades safely

SCOPE
- Single-bot, single-domain responsibility
- Deterministic behavior under retries, restarts, and partial failures
- API-driven systems (REST / RPC / GraphQL)
- No UI, no human-in-the-loop assumptions

NON-GOALS
- Multi-tenant orchestration
- Credential provisioning
- Secret storage implementation
- UI / UX concerns


==================================================
1. EXECUTION MODEL
==================================================

BOT_PROPERTIES:
- Event-driven or scheduled
- Long-running process
- Must survive partial failures
- Must not require manual intervention

CORE_RULES:
- Bot MUST remain alive under all recoverable errors
- Bot MUST NOT crash due to external system failures
- Bot MUST NOT block indefinitely
- Bot MUST NOT assume correctness of external systems


==================================================
2. RUNTIME ASSERTIONS (NASA POWER OF 10)
==================================================

RUNTIME_ASSERTIONS:
- A1: All function inputs MUST be validated at entry
- A2: All external API responses MUST be validated before use
- A3: All state invariants MUST be asserted immediately after any mutation
- A4: No unbounded loops permitted (all loops must have static upper bounds)
- A5: All retries MUST be bounded and externally visible via logs
- A6: No dynamic code execution or reflection
- A7: Runtime assertions MUST remain enabled in production

ASSERTION_RULES:
- Assertions enforce invariants and safety guarantees
- Assertions are NOT tests
- Assertions live inside production code
- Assertion failure = controlled degradation, never crash


==================================================
3. DEGRADATION MODEL (AUTONOMY)
==================================================

DEGRADATION_MODES:
- MODE_NORMAL: full functionality
- MODE_RETRYING: transient failure recovery
- MODE_READ_ONLY: no mutating operations
- MODE_IDLE_SAFE: bot alive, zero external calls

DEGRADATION_TRANSITIONS:
- Repeated transient failures → MODE_RETRYING
- Retry exhaustion → MODE_READ_ONLY
- Unrecoverable system condition → MODE_IDLE_SAFE
- Explicit recovery condition → MODE_NORMAL

DEGRADATION_INVARIANTS:
- No state mutation outside MODE_NORMAL
- MODE_READ_ONLY permits only read operations
- MODE_IDLE_SAFE performs no external calls
- Mode transitions MUST be logged


==================================================
4. IDEMPOTENCY CONTRACT (MANDATORY)
==================================================

IDEMPOTENCY_RULES:
- All mutating operations MUST be idempotent
- Replayed or duplicated events MUST NOT alter final state
- Retries MUST NOT introduce side effects
- State transitions MUST be deterministic given identical inputs

IDEMPOTENCY_INVARIANTS:
- Re-executing the same event yields the same state
- Bot restart + replay yields identical state
- External calls MUST tolerate duplicate execution


==================================================
5. ERROR MODEL
==================================================

ERROR_CLASSES:
- TRANSIENT_ERROR: recoverable (timeouts, 5xx, network)
- PERMANENT_ERROR: non-recoverable (schema violation, contract breach)
- INTERNAL_ERROR: logic or invariant violation

ERROR_HANDLING_RULES:
- TRANSIENT_ERROR → retry with backoff
- PERMANENT_ERROR → degrade, never retry blindly
- INTERNAL_ERROR → assert, degrade, continue safely

ERROR_INVARIANTS:
- No error may crash the bot
- No error may block the main loop
- All errors MUST be logged with context


==================================================
6. RETRY & BACKOFF STRATEGY
==================================================

RETRY_POLICY:
- Library: tenacity
- Strategy: exponential backoff with jitter
- Retries MUST be bounded
- Retry attempts MUST be logged

RETRY_RULES:
- Retries allowed ONLY for transient errors
- Retry exhaustion MUST trigger degradation
- No infinite retries under any condition


==================================================
7. CONCURRENCY & STATE SAFETY
==================================================

CONCURRENCY_RULES:
- Single authority per mutable state
- No shared mutable state without explicit control
- State mutations MUST be atomic

STATE_INVARIANTS:
- State is always internally consistent
- Partial updates are forbidden
- Failed operations MUST leave state unchanged


==================================================
8. OBSERVABILITY CONTRACT
==================================================

LOGGING_RULES:
- Structured logging only
- No silent failures
- No log spam loops

MINIMUM_LOG_EVENTS:
- Mode transitions
- Retry attempts and exhaustion
- Assertion failures
- External call failures

METRICS (MINIMUM):
- error_rate
- retry_count
- time_in_each_degradation_mode
- successful_operations_count


==================================================
9. DESIGN CONSTRAINTS
==================================================

DESIGN_RULES:
- Business logic MUST be isolated from infrastructure
- External systems are always assumed unreliable
- Explicit is mandatory; implicit behavior forbidden
- Defaults MUST be safe, conservative, and bounded

FORBIDDEN:
- God classes
- Hidden global state
- Implicit retries
- Silent exception swallowing


==================================================
10. TERMINAL GUARANTEES
==================================================

GUARANTEES:
- Bot never crashes due to external failures
- Bot never corrupts state
- Bot behavior is predictable and repeatable
- Bot degrades safely instead of failing
- Bot can be restarted without side effects
